text.__SUMMARY__: Common names: Ecuadorian annulated tree boa.Corallus annulatus blombergi is a non-venomous Boinae subspecies found in Pacific Ecuador.
text.Description: Medium-sized, not much is known about its natural history.
text.Taxonomy: Regarded as a full species, C. blombergi, by some experts, primarily due to its significantly different bone morphology, color and scalation.
